# Deploying Your Backend to Railway

Your code changes are done. Now follow these steps in your browser.

## Step 1 — Push your code to GitHub first
Your Railway app needs to pull the code from GitHub. Make sure your latest code is pushed.

## Step 2 — Log into Railway
Go to [railway.app](https://railway.app) and log in to your account.

## Step 3 — Create a New Service
1. Click **"New Project"**
2. Select **"Deploy from GitHub repo"**
3. Select your `SoloSuccess-AI` repository
4. When it asks for the **Root Directory**, type: `server`
5. Click **Deploy**

Railway will detect the `Dockerfile` and build your server automatically.

## Step 4 — Add Environment Variables in Railway
Once deployed, click on your service → **"Variables"** tab → add each one:

| Variable | Value |
|---|---|
| `NODE_ENV` | `production` |
| `DATABASE_URL` | *(copy from `server/.env`)* |
| `JWT_SECRET` | *(make a strong random string — use [randomkeygen.com](https://randomkeygen.com))* |
| `CLIENT_URL` | `https://solosuccessai.fun` |
| `GEMINI_API_KEY` | *(copy from `server/.env`)* |
| `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL` | *(copy from `server/.env`)* |
| `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN` | *(copy from `server/.env`)* |
| `SENTRY_DSN` | *(copy from `server/index.ts` line 38)* |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The `JWT_SECRET` you set in Railway **must also be set in Vercel** with the same value. Both sides need to match.

## Step 5 — Get Your Railway URL
After deploy completes, go to **"Settings"** → **"Domains"** → copy the URL (looks like `https://solosuccess-api.up.railway.app`).

Test it: open `https://your-railway-url/api/health` in your browser — you should see `{"status":"ok","websocket":"active",...}`.

## Step 6 — Add Variables in Vercel
Go to your Vercel project → **Settings** → **Environment Variables** → add:

| Variable | Value |
|---|---|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SOCKET_URL` | Your Railway URL from Step 5 |
| `JWT_SECRET` | Same value you set in Railway |

Then click **Redeploy** in Vercel.

## That's It! ✅
Real-time notifications will now work. When a user gets a new notification, a toast will appear instantly without needing to refresh.
